    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Selective School Prayer</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard Rosenthal letter comments on September 2 article on prayers at high school football games</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Prayer Comes First, but Football Game Is the Main Event'' (news article, Sept. 2):</p>
        <p>If prayer at football games is good and right, why don't church and civic leaders, townspeople, school officials and radio personalities agitate for it at school track meets, chess and debate matches and school plays, dances and exams?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Prayer Comes First, but Football Game Is the Main Event'' (news article, Sept. 2):</p>
        <p>If prayer at football games is good and right, why don't church and civic leaders, townspeople, school officials and radio personalities agitate for it at school track meets, chess and debate matches and school plays, dances and exams?</p>
        <p>Do they think these participants and spectators are less deserving of divine beneficence, or aren't the turnouts at those events large enough to make it worth going to the trouble to flout the Supreme Court in order to campaign and proselytize?</p>
        <p>RICHARD ROSENTHAL  New York, Sept. 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
